      • cleanup

        public void cleanup()
        Description copied from interface: BigMap
        Removes all obsolete internal references that are no longer referencing valid objects. A cleanup does not alter the content of the List as it is seen from the outside. However, a long-living BigList might waste memory after some time if there are many SoftReferences left that are no longer pointing to valid objects in memory. Periodically doing a cleanup might help keeping memory consumptions lower.
        Specified by:
        cleanup in interface BigMap<K,V>
